Chelicerae
(
Fig. 13
). Dorsal edge of movable cheliceral finger with two subdistal (
sd
) denticles. Ventral edge is smooth, with well-developed serrula on distal half. Fixed cheliceral finger with four denticles: basal, median, subdistal and distal. Basal and median denticles forked. Typical for genus.
